  "text": "Pretreatment of the mycelial powder Prior to the extraction of the polysaccharides, a supercritical fluid carbon dioxide (SC-CO 2 , 99.5% in purity) extraction was performed to remove some inherently existing oil soluble substances in order to minimize the interference to the polysaccharides, according to a previous report [CITATION_1] . Briefly, 100 g of the lyophilized mycelial powder was weighed and added with 5% n-hexane to serve as a modifier. The extraction was carried out at 60 °C and 5000 psi in a supercritical gluid extraction apparatus (ISCO SFX TM 2-10, Isco, Lincoln, NE, USA) attached with a modified extraction vessel. In the beginning, a dynamic continuous extraction was adopted at a flow rate of 1 mL SC-CO 2 /min for 1 h, and was then followed by a static extraction for an additional l h. The oil soluble extracts were collected in 95% ethanol. The residue (ACR 1 ) remaining in the extraction vessel was used in the subsequent experimentations.",
